<!--
  PROFILE CUSTOM CONTENT SNIPPET

  Adds the Inklings tab content to the character profile page.

  FILE: ares-webportal/app/components/profile-custom.hbs

  INSTALLATION:

  1. Open your game's ares-webportal/app/components/profile-custom.hbs
  2. Copy the code block below this comment:
     - If the file is empty or nearly empty, paste it as-is
     - If the file already has other tab-pane divs, add it after the closing </div> of
       another tab-pane entry (maintain the existing indentation and structure)

  IMPORTANT DETAILS:

  ID MATCHING:
  - The id="inklings-tab-pane" MUST match the href in profile-custom-tabs.snippet.hbs
  - Do NOT change this value

  PROPERTY NAMES:
  - These must match the property names used in your profile-custom.hbs
  - If your profile uses "character" instead of "char", update all instances
  - If profile-custom.hbs is otherwise empty (nothing to compare against),
    check whatever file invokes it instead - e.g. profile.hbs or profile-
    system.hbs, wherever you see <ProfileCustom @char={{...}} ... /> (or the
    older {{profile-custom char=... }} syntax) - the argument name used
    there (@char / @character) is the one this component actually receives.
    Do NOT assume a "viewer" argument exists just because "char" does - see
    VIEWER IDENTITY below.

  REQUIRED BACKEND SETUP:
  - You must also install the get_fields_for_viewing hook from
    custom-install/custom_char_fields.snippet.rb (Step 2) or the type
    dropdown will be empty and staff won't see their permission override.

  APPROVAL STATUS - char.custom.is_approved, NOT char.is_approved:
  - The base character data the web portal sends for a profile page has
    no "is_approved"/"approved" field at all (confirmed against
    plugins/profile/web/character_request_handler.rb's profile_data hash -
    it isn't in there). "isApproved=this.char.is_approved" below would
    silently be undefined for every character, all the time - not a typo
    you'd notice, since undefined just renders as nothing, not an error.
  - Approval status must come through the SAME get_fields_for_viewing hook
    as the other custom fields on this line (can_manage_inklings,
    inkling_types) - see custom_char_fields.snippet.rb, which now also
    sets fields[:is_approved] = char.is_approved?. Reference it as
    this.char.custom.is_approved, not this.char.is_approved.

  VIEWER IDENTITY - there is no "this.viewer" object:
  - Confirmed against the real base template (the one that invokes this
    component, e.g. <ProfileCustom @char={{this.char}} @game={{this.game}}
    @onReloadChar={{this.reloadChar}} />): only "char" (the profile being
    viewed) and "game" get passed down. There is no separate "viewer"
    character object anywhere in this component or its parent - Ares
    computes viewer-relative permissions server-side and bakes them
    directly into the char payload (e.g. char.can_manage, char.can_approve)
    instead of shipping a second character object for the client to
    compare against. "this.viewer.id" below would always be undefined,
    which silently makes both viewerId and isSelf wrong for every
    character, every time - the same "undefined renders as nothing, not an
    error" trap as the is_approved issue above.
  - The logged-in viewer's id must come through the SAME
    get_fields_for_viewing hook (it already receives both char AND viewer
    as Ruby method parameters server-side, even though the client never
    sees a viewer object) - see custom_char_fields.snippet.rb, which now
    also sets fields[:viewer_id] = viewer ? viewer.id : nil. Reference it
    as this.char.custom.viewer_id, not this.viewer.id, in BOTH the
    viewerId argument and the isSelf comparison below.

  WEB PORTAL OPTIONAL:
  - This component is entirely optional - if you're running MUSH-only,
    you do not need this snippet or the related components at all.
-->

<div class="tab-pane fade" id="inklings-tab-pane">
  {{inklings-tab characterId=this.char.id characterName=this.char.name viewerId=this.char.custom.viewer_id isStaff=this.char.custom.can_manage_inklings isApproved=this.char.custom.is_approved isSelf=(eq this.char.id this.char.custom.viewer_id) typeInfo=this.char.custom.inkling_types}}
</div>
